      "abstract": "A maximizing function, f, is shown to exist for the HLS inequality on R': 11 IXI - * fIq < Np f A , Iif IIwith Nbeing the sharp constant and i/p + X/n = 1 + 1/q, 1 <p, q, n/X < x. When p =q' or p = 2 or q = 2, f and N are explicitly evaluated. A maximizing f is also shown to exist for other inequalities: (i) The Okikiolu, Glaser, Martin, Grosse, Thirring inequality: Kn vjj Vf 11?2 11 IIx-bfjIp, n ? 3, 0 < b < 1, p = 2n/(2b + n - 2). (This was known before, but the proof here has certain simplifications.) (ii) The doubly weighted HLS inequality of Stein and Weiss:"
